ilms]]\n[[Category:British multilingual films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Luigi Zampa]]\n{{1940s-drama-film-stub}}\n{{1940s-UK-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Children_of_Chance_(1949_film)"}
{"title_page": "Cornwallis Maude, 1st Viscount Hawarden", "text_new": "{{short description|Anglo-Irish politician and peer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use Irish English|date=January 2020}}\n'''Cornwallis Maude, 1st Viscount Hawarden''' (19 September 1729 \u2013 23 August 1803) was an [[Anglo-Irish]] peer and politician.<ref name=\"burke\">{{cite book |title= [[Burke's Peerage|Burke's Peerage, Baronetage & Knighthood]]|publisher=Burke's Peerage & Gentry |editor= Mosley, Charles |editorlink=Charles Mosley (genealogist) |edition=107 |year= 2003 |page= 1826 |ref=Burke |isbn=0-9711966-2-1}}</ref>\n\nHawarden was the second son of [[Sir Robert Maude, 1st Baronet]] and his wife, Eleanor Cornwallis, daughter of Thomas Cornwallis.<ref name=\"burke\"/> \n\nHawarden succeeded to the baronetcy following the death of his unmarried older brother, [[Thomas Maude, 1st Baron de Montalt]], in 1777. He served as the Member of Parliament for [[Roscommon Borough (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Roscommon Borough]] in the [[Irish House of Commons]] between 1783 and 1785. He was created '''Baron de Montalt''' of Hawarden in the [[Peerage of Ireland]] on 29 June 1785. He was further honoured when he was created '''Viscount Hawarden''', also in the Peerage of Ireland, on 5 December 1793.<ref name=\"burke\"/>\n\nHe had 16 children with three wives.<ref name=\"burke\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|ie}}\n{{s-bef\n | before=[[Henry Sandford, 1st Baron Mount Sandford|Henry Moore Sandford]]\n | before2=[[Robert Sandford (1722\u20131793)|Robert Sandford]]\n}}\n{{s-ttl\n |title=[[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|Member of Parliament]] for [[Roscommon Borough (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Roscommon Borough]]\n |years=1783\u20131785\n | with = [[George Sandford, 3rd Baron Mount Sandford|George Sandford]]\n}}\n{{s-aft\n |after=[[Maurice Copinger]]\n |after2=[[George Sandford, 3rd Baron Mount Sandford|George Sandford]]\n}}\n\n{{s-reg|ie}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Viscount Hawarden]] | before= New creation| after=[[Thomas Ralph Maude, 2nd Viscount Hawarden|Thomas Ralph Maude]]| years= 1793&ndash;1803 }}\n{{succession box | title=[[Baron de Montalt]] | before= New creation| after=[[Thomas Ralph Maude, 2nd Viscount Hawarden|Thomas Ralph Maude]]| years= 1785&ndash;1803 }}\n{{s-reg|ie-bt}}\n{{s-bef |before=[[Thomas Maude, 1st Baron de Montalt|Thomas Maude]]}}\n{{s-ttl |title=[[Maude Baronets|Baronet]]<br />'''(of Dundrum) | years='''1777&ndash;1803}}\n{{s-aft |after=[[Thomas Ralph Maude, 2nd Viscount Hawarden|Thomas Ralph Maude]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hawarden, Cornwallis Maude, 1st Viscount}}\n[[Category:1729 births]]\n[[Category:1803 deaths]]\n[[Category:Viscounts in the Peerage of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Irish MPs 1783\u20131790]]\n[[Category:Anglo-Irish people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Ireland (pre-1801) for County Roscommon constituencies]]\n[[Category:Peers of Ireland created by George III]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Anglo-Irish politician and peer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use Irish English|date=January 2020}}\n'''Cornwallis Maude, 1st Viscount Hawarden''' (19 September 1729 \u2013 23 August 1803) was an [[Anglo-Irish]] peer and politician.<ref name=\"burke\">{{cite book |title= [[Burke's Peerage|Burke's Peerage, Baronetage & Knighthood]]|publisher=Burke's Peerage & Gentry |editor= Mosley, Charles |editorlink=Charles Mosley (genealogist) |edition=107 |year= 2003 |page= 1826 |ref=Burke |isbn=0-9711966-2-1}}</ref>\n\nHawarden was the second son of [[Maude Baronets|Sir Robert Maude, 1st Baronet]] and his wife, Eleanor Cornwallis, daughter of Thomas Cornwallis.<ref name=\"burke\"/> \n\nHawarden succeeded to the baronetcy following the death of his unmarried older brother, [[Thomas Maude, 1st Baron de Montalt]], in 1777. He served as the Member of Parliament for [[Roscommon Borough (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Roscommon Borough]] in the [[Irish House of Commons]] between 1783 and 1785. He was created '''Baron de Montalt''' of Hawarden in the [[Peerage of Ireland]] on 29 June 1785. He was further honoured when he was created '''Viscount Hawarden''', also in the Peerage of Ireland, on 5 December 1793.<ref name=\"burke\"/>\n\nHe had 16 children with three wives.<ref name=\"burke\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|ie}}\n{{s-bef\n | before=[[Henry Sandford, 1st Baron Mount Sandford|Henry Moore Sandford]]\n | before2=[[Robert Sandford (1722\u20131793)|Robert Sandford]]\n}}\n{{s-ttl\n |title=[[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|Member of Parliament]] for [[Roscommon Borough (Parliament of Ireland constituency)|Roscommon Borough]]\n |years=1783\u20131785\n | with = [[George Sandford, 3rd Baron Mount Sandford|George Sandford]]\n}}\n{{s-aft\n |after=[[Maurice Copinger]]\n |after2=[[George Sandford, 3rd Baron Mount Sandford|George Sandford]]\n}}\n\n{{s-reg|ie}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Viscount Hawarden]] | before= New creation| after=[[Thomas Ralph Maude, 2nd Viscount Hawarden|Thomas Ralph Maude]]| years= 1793&ndash;1803 }}\n{{succession box | title=[[Baron de Montalt]] | before= New creation| after=[[Thomas Ralph Maude, 2nd Viscount Hawarden|Thomas Ralph Maude]]| years= 1785&ndash;1803 }}\n{{s-reg|ie-bt}}\n{{s-bef |before=[[Thomas Maude, 1st Baron de Montalt|Thomas Maude]]}}\n{{s-ttl |title=[[Maude Baronets|Baronet]]<br />'''(of Dundrum) | years='''1777&ndash;1803}}\n{{s-aft |after=[[Thomas Ralph Maude, 2nd Viscount Hawarden|Thomas Ralph Maude]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hawarden, Cornwallis Maude, 1st Viscount}}\n[[Category:1729 births]]\n[[Category:1803 deaths]]\n[[Category:Viscounts in the Peerage of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Irish MPs 1783\u20131790]]\n[[Category:Anglo-Irish people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Parliament of Ireland (pre-1801) for County Roscommon constituencies]]\n[[Category:Peers of Ireland created by George III]]\n", "name_user": "WatermillockCommon", "label": "safe",